      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The change in the Hebrew, as in the English, from verbs in the infinitive to substantives is probably intended to emphasize the completion of the list. The words are of course closely connected with the “love” and “hate” of the preceding clause, but differ in referring to the wider range of national relations. Here also the wisdom of a king or statesman lies in discerning the opportuneness of war or peace, in seeing when the maxim “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "si vis pacem para bellum",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "” is applicable or inapplicable.",
        "children": []
      },
